{"name": "aionotify", "metadata": {"name": "aionotify", "version": "0.3.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules", "Topic :: System :: Filesystems"], "home_page": "https://github.com/rbarrois/aionotify", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Asyncio-powered inotify library", "upload_time": 1715792727}, "documentation": ["# aionotify\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/aionotify.svg\n:alt: Latest Version\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/aionotify/\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/aionotify.svg\n:alt: Supported Python versions\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/aionotify/\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/wheel/aionotify.svg\n:alt: Wheel status\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/aionotify/\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/aionotify.svg\n:alt: License\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/aionotify/\n```\n\n`aionotify` is a simple, asyncio-based inotify library.\n\nIts use is quite simple:\n\n```python\nimport asyncio\nimport aionotify\n\n# Setup the watcher\nwatcher = aionotify.Watcher()\nwatcher.watch(alias='logs', path='/var/log', flags=aionotify.Flags.MODIFY)\n\nasync def work():\n    await watcher.setup()\n    for _i in range(10):\n        # Pick the 10 first events\n        event = await watcher.get_event()\n        print(event)\n    watcher.close()\n\nasyncio.run(work())\n```\n\n## Links\n\n- Code at <https://github.com/rbarrois/aionotify>\n- Package at <https://pypi.python.org/pypi/aionotify/>\n- Continuous integration at <https://travis-ci.org/rbarrois/aionotify/>\n\n## Events\n\nAn event is a simple object with a few attributes:\n\n- `name`: the path of the modified file\n- `flags`: the modification flag; use `aionotify.Flags.parse()` to retrieve a list of individual values.\n- `alias`: the alias of the watch triggering the event\n- `cookie`: for renames, this integer value links the \"renamed from\" and \"renamed to\" events.\n\n## Watches\n\n`aionotify` uses a system of \"watches\", similar to inotify.\n\nA watch may have an alias; by default, it uses the path name:\n\n```python\nwatcher = aionotify.Watcher()\nwatcher.watch('/var/log', flags=aionotify.Flags.MODIFY)\n\n# Similar to:\nwatcher.watch('/var/log', flags=aionotify.Flags.MODIFY, alias='/var/log')\n```\n\nA watch can be removed by using its alias:\n\n```python\nwatcher = aionotify.Watcher()\nwatcher.watch('/var/log', flags=aionotify.Flags.MODIFY)\n\nwatcher.unwatch('/var/log')\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "aionotify", "documentation": ["Copyright (c) 2016 The aionotify project", "This code is distributed under the two-clause BSD License."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "aionotify.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aionotify.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "aionotify.Flags", "xref": {"fqname": "aionotify.enums.Flags", "project": null}}, {"name": "aionotify.Watcher", "xref": {"fqname": "aionotify.base.Watcher", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums", "documentation": ["Copyright (c) 2016 The aionotify project", "This code is distributed under the two-clause BSD License."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags", "bases": ["enum.IntEnum"], "methods": [{"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.parse", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "flags", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.ACCESS", "type": null, "documentation": [": File was accessed"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.MODIFY", "type": null, "documentation": [": File was modified"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.ATTRIB", "type": null, "documentation": [": Metadata changed"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.CLOSE_WRITE", "type": null, "documentation": [": Writable file was closed"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.CLOSE_NOWRITE", "type": null, "documentation": [": Unwritable file closed"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.OPEN", "type": null, "documentation": [": File was opened"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.MOVED_FROM", "type": null, "documentation": [": File was moved from X"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.MOVED_TO", "type": null, "documentation": [": File was moved to Y"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.CREATE", "type": null, "documentation": [": Subfile was created"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.DELETE", "type": null, "documentation": [": Subfile was deleted"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.DELETE_SELF", "type": null, "documentation": [": Self was deleted"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.MOVE_SELF", "type": null, "documentation": [": Self was moved"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.UNMOUNT", "type": null, "documentation": [": Backing fs was unmounted"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.Q_OVERFLOW", "type": null, "documentation": [": Event queue overflowed"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.IGNORED", "type": null, "documentation": [": File was ignored"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.ONLYDIR", "type": null, "documentation": [": only watch the path if it is a directory"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.DONT_FOLLOW", "type": null, "documentation": [": don't follow a sym link"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.EXCL_UNLINK", "type": null, "documentation": [": exclude events on unlinked objects"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.MASK_ADD", "type": null, "documentation": [": add to the mask of an already existing watch"]}, {"name": "aionotify.enums.Flags.ISDIR", "type": null, "documentation": [": event occu